# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Research Engine deploy — environment template.
# Copy to .env and fill in. Never commit the real .env.
#   cp .env.example .env
#   chmod 600 .env
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# REQUIRED — HMAC root for every signed event token. Stable forever.
# Generate once and back up out-of-band; losing it makes every prior
# signed token unverifiable.
#   $(openssl rand -hex 32)
AXIOM_MASTER_KEY=

# REQUIRED for the TLS profile — the public DNS name that points at
# this box. Add a CNAME / A record before bringing the stack up.
# Caddy uses this for ACME (Let's Encrypt) cert provisioning.
RESEARCH_HOST=research.orivael.dev

# REQUIRED for the TLS profile — Caddy basic_auth pairs. One pair per
# beta tester. Format is whitespace-separated "user $hash" pairs, all
# on a single line.
#
# Generate hashes one at a time:
#   docker run --rm caddy:2-alpine caddy hash-password
# (it prompts for the password and prints the bcrypt hash)
#
# Then assemble:
#   BETA_AUTH_HASHES="alice $2a$14$AAAA... bob $2a$14$BBBB... carol $2a$14$CCCC..."
#
# To rotate a single tester out: regenerate the env with that pair
# removed and `docker compose up -d caddy` (caddy reloads the Caddyfile).
BETA_AUTH_HASHES=

# OPTIONAL — bearer-token defense-in-depth on /api/* paths.
# When set, EVERY /api/research, /api/medical/research, /api/ledger
# request must carry: Authorization: Bearer <this value>
# Leave blank to rely solely on Caddy basic-auth. For a slow beta with
# trusted testers, blank is fine.
AXIOM_RESEARCH_TOKEN=

# ── LLM backend ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pick ONE backend by setting AXIOM_BACKEND. Valid values:
#   deepseek  — hosted, OpenAI-compatible, cheapest for solo beta
#   nim       — NVIDIA NIM, broad model catalog, free tier at build.nvidia.com
#   local     — Ollama (on the box via host.docker.internal, or on a
#               reachable laptop/phone via tailscale / LAN URL)
#   custom    — any OpenAI-compatible endpoint (OpenRouter, Together,
#               LM Studio, vLLM, …)
#
# Each backend reads its OWN env-var triple. Only the block matching
# AXIOM_BACKEND is consumed — others are ignored. Switching backends
# is a one-line edit + `docker compose up -d --build research`.

# ─── deepseek (default — cheapest sane combo) ────────────────────────
# Roughly $5-15/month for solo-founder volume; ~$30/month with ~10 testers.
AXIOM_BACKEND=deepseek
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat

# ─── nim (NVIDIA NIM) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# To switch: set AXIOM_BACKEND=nim above, fill in these two, comment
# out the DEEPSEEK_* lines (or leave them — they're ignored).
# Find the EXACT model slug at https://build.nvidia.com → your model
# → "Model API" tab. Wrong slug returns 404 at request time, not boot.
#
# AXIOM_BACKEND=nim
# NVIDIA_NIM_API_KEY=nvapi-...
# NIM_MODEL=meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct
#   # Other good picks:
#   #   nvidia/llama-3.1-nemotron-70b-instruct
#   #   mistralai/mixtral-8x7b-instruct-v0.1
#   #   deepseek-ai/deepseek-r1
#   #   minimaxai/minimax-m1

# ─── local (Ollama on this box, or laptop/phone via URL) ─────────────
# Most common: a GGUF you fine-tuned in Colab, imported via
# `ollama create axiom-qwen -f Modelfile` on this box.
# The extra_hosts line in docker-compose.yml makes host.docker.internal
# resolve to the docker host (i.e. Ollama running on this box).
#
# AXIOM_BACKEND=local
# OLLAMA_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=axiom-qwen
#   # For a laptop/phone-hosted Ollama on tailscale, swap the URL:
#   # OLLAMA_URL=http://your-laptop.tailnet.ts.net:11434

# ─── custom (any OpenAI-compatible endpoint) ─────────────────────────
# AXIOM_BACKEND=custom
# AXIOM_API_KEY=...
# AXIOM_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# AXIOM_MODEL=anthropic/claude-3.5-sonnet

# ─── Legacy OpenAI-compatible client (Prompt Evolution + DSL tabs) ───
# Only `ui.py` reads these — the Re:Search engine does NOT. Leave
# blank unless you're also running the Streamlit UI on this host.
# When set, they default to whatever AXIOM_BACKEND points at.
AXIOM_API_KEY=
AXIOM_BASE_URL=
AXIOM_MODEL=

# ── Per-domain LLM routing (optional) ─────────────────────────────────
# The console's domain selector (Medical / Finance / Security / HR /
# Supply Chain / General) can route to a different backend per domain.
# Anything not overridden falls through to the default backend above.
# When ANY of these is set, /api/health reports a routing summary like
# "domain-routed · default=X · medical=Y · security=Z".
#
# Each domain needs its own AXIOM_BACKEND_<DOM>; the *_URL / *_KEY /
# *_MODEL suffix is optional and falls back to the bare env vars
# (AXIOM_BASE_URL, AXIOM_API_KEY, AXIOM_MODEL) when missing.
#
# Example: medically-tuned model for Medical, coder-tuned for Security.
#
# AXIOM_BACKEND_MEDICAL=custom
# AXIOM_BASE_URL_MEDICAL=https://your-medical-llm/v1
# AXIOM_API_KEY_MEDICAL=
# AXIOM_MODEL_MEDICAL=meditron-70b
#
# AXIOM_BACKEND_SECURITY=custom
# AXIOM_BASE_URL_SECURITY=https://your-coder-llm/v1
# AXIOM_API_KEY_SECURITY=
# AXIOM_MODEL_SECURITY=qwen2.5-coder-32b

# ── Per-domain retrieval corpora (optional) ───────────────────────────
# Independent of per-domain LLM routing above. The console's domain
# selector can also pick a different document corpus per domain — a
# Medical query searches only the medical literature, a Security query
# only the security docs, etc. Anything not overridden falls through
# to the default repo-wide corpus (docs/, README.md, patents/).
#
# Comma-separated paths add multiple roots to the same domain corpus.
# Missing paths are logged and skipped at boot (not a fatal error).
#
# AXIOM_RETRIEVAL_DIR_MEDICAL=/data/corpora/pubmed,/data/corpora/guidelines
# AXIOM_RETRIEVAL_DIR_SECURITY=/data/corpora/cve,/data/corpora/owasp
# AXIOM_RETRIEVAL_DIR_FINANCE=/data/corpora/sec-edgar
# AXIOM_RETRIEVAL_DIR_HR=/data/corpora/employment-law
# AXIOM_RETRIEVAL_DIR_SUPPLY_CHAIN=/data/corpora/sap-logs
